"n.茅舍；肮脏的小屋 【英】 n. 茅舍；肮脏的小屋(an y small, miserable dwelling; hut) 【考】 palatial : hovel / bucolic : city(富丽堂皇对小屋/乡 村对城市) n. (简陋而不适于居住的)小屋 = dwelling = hut 【记】读: 好味儿－又臭又脏的小屋 【类】palatial: hovel = bucolic: city 富丽堂皇的对简陋小屋 = 乡村的对城市 【记】hole + 音：屋→山洞一样的屋；音：猴窝，猴屋；音：后屋，前屋很大很宽畅，后屋是茅舍，很脏； hovel (n.)  mid-14c., ""roofed passage, vent for smoke,"" later ""shed for animals"" (mid-15c.), of unknown origin. Meaning ""shed for human habitation; rude or miserable cabin"" is from 1620s. It also sometimes meant ""canopied niche for a statue or image"" (mid-15c.)."
